                <header class="article-header">
                    <h1 itemprop="name"><a class="article-title" href="/post/21-04-23-hund-flq75/">Hund FLQ75 Repairs</a></h1>
                </header>
                
                <div class="article-meta">
                    <a href="/post/21-04-23-hund-flq75/" class="article-date">
                        <time datetime='2023-04-21T00:32:44.000&#43;02:00' itemprop="datePublished">2023-04-21</time>
                    </a>
                    
                    
                    
                </div>
                <div class="article-entry" itemprop="articleBody">
                    <p>
                        <a class="article-title" href="/post/21-04-23-hund-flq75/"><img width=1000 height=100 alt="Banner" src="/post/21-04-23-hund-flq75//banner.jpg"></a><br>
                    Circuitry Overview The circuit is super simple, there is a motor run capacitor for the AC fan which is connected to a separate tap on the transformer and insulated from the rest of the circuitry. A small triac dimmer on the secondary 12V AC side using a MAC223 triac and another 3 pin TO-92 device which I think is either another triac or a SCR two film capacitors and a couple potentiometers.
                    </p>
                    <p class="article-more-link">
                        <a href="/post/21-04-23-hund-flq75/">Read More</a>
                    </p>
                </div>

                
